  "text": "The Lower Liaohe River Plain (LLRP), is located in the Northeast Plain, one of China's four great plains. It is an important industrial area for both Liaoning Province and the whole of the northeast region, and is a designated regional representative site in the Chinese Ecosystem Research Network [CITATION_1] . However, as the economy has developed rapidly in recent years, issues of water pollution and water quality deterioration have emerged to varying degrees [CITATION_2] , therefore, assessing the groundwater environmental risk in the region is very necessary.",
